# Orders

## Create Authenticated Tracking Uri

```ruby
require 'xpo'

api = Xpo::APIClient.authorize!('XPO_AUTH_KEY')
api.orders.authentictedTrackingUri(ORDER_ID)
```

```python
import xpo

api = xpo.authorize('XPO_AUTH_KEY')
api.orders.authentictedTrackingUri(ORDER_ID)
```

```shell
curl "h<%= config[:host] %>orders/<ID>/authenticted-tracking-uri?bu=<BU>"
  -X DELETE
  -H "Authorization: XPO_AUTH_KEY"
```

```javascript
const xpo = require('xpo');

let api = xpo.authorize('XPO_AUTH_KEY');
let response = api.orders.authentictedTrackingUri(ORDER_ID);
```

> JSON Response:

```json
{
  "orderId": 'ORDER_ID',
  "uri" : "https://track.xpo.com/?orderid=..."
}
```

This endpoint can be used to generate an authentucated URI for the XPO Logistics tracking page

### HTTP Request

`POST <%= config[:host] %>orders/<ID>/authenticted-tracking-uri?bu=<BU>`

### URL Parameters

Parameter | Description |  Valid Values |
--------- | ----------- | ---------------- |
ID | The id of the order | - |
BU | The business unit the order belongs to | [Business Units](#business-units) |
